cs.NI, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.SY, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper discusses vehicular communication networks and their potential to enhance automated driving vehicles. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of sensors and processors in automated driving vehicles. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is mentioned in the abstract as one of the advanced sensors used in automated driving vehicles. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is mentioned in the abstract as the automated driving vehicles are capable of conducting automobile operation. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) may also be relevant as the paper discusses the security and privacy concerns in vehicular communication networks.
